<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="411" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,966,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1758,1783]" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">Comments</emphasis>
. Recently 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morgan" authorityYear="1913" box="[450,557,1759,1782]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Leucothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piercei">
<emphasis box="[450,557,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">L. piercei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from Argentina, and damage to the leaves of pepper (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Capsicum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="411" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="annuum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">Capsicum annuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by this species was recognised for the first time (
<bibRefCitation author="Zamar" box="[824,1036,1794,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="411" refString="Zamar, M. I., de Borbon, C. M., Aguirre, A., Mino, V. &amp; Caceres, S. (2014) First record of damage Leucothrips piercei (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) in pepper crops (Capsicum annuum L. (Solanaceae) in Argentina. Revista de la Facultad de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad Nacional de Cuyo, 46 (1), 213 - 219." type="journal article" year="2014">
Zamar 
<emphasis box="[908,959,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
). In Okinawa, however, damage to crops is apparently not conspicuous.
</paragraph>
